item.description:
Udev rules We want to make sure the target hard drive is always assigned to the pre-defined block device name. First collect information about the hard drive, supposed for now current block device name is /dev/sda, and idProduct is the attribute with which this device can be identified.
udevadm info -a /dev/sda | grep -i &quot;idProduct&quot;
Then create udev rules file to let the system make a symlink whenever this device is attached.
